>Description:
The ESC key closes the find dialog box when using
the "separate", "floating" version of the find dialog
box. I expected ESC key the hide the "docked" version of the box,
but it doesn't.

Both boxes also help underscored keyboard shortcuts on the buttons.
>How-To-Repeat:
edit/preferences
editing/general, turn off the option "use separate dialog for searching"
ctrl-f  (shows the search box)
esc (does not do anthing)
>Fix:
